column2:
HAHA...Biggest Joke!! DEAR GAMERS, PLEASE DON'T BE FOOLED!!

I'm just writing this to help educate people about buying a graphics card.

First of all, people are repeatedly fooled into buying cheap low end GPU's like this one, just because it has "2 GB" of VRAM. Let me tell you, for this weak GPU chip, even 512MB is more than enough.

Large VRAM's above 1GB are only usefull if ur gaming at a screen resolution higher than 1368x768, and when using high AA (Anti-Aliasing) settings. The funny thing is that this GPU is so weak, that it will totally choke and suffocate if you try running any game modern game at even 4x AA :)

If you don't believe me, just google search 'How much ram does your graphics card really need'. Open the first link by TomsHardware, and then see d test results for various games using 512MB, 1GB & 2GB of VRAM. Then you'll realize the truth :)

Only buy 2GB cards if you have a screen resolution of 1920x1080 or more, and have a powerfull enough GPU that can support AA while maintaining atleast 40+ FPS.

FOR BUDGET GAMERS,get 1GB DDR3 Radeon HD6670 OR GeForce 630 ATLEAST.

How to understand Graphic Card Model Numbers?
================================

Both nVidia and ATi/AMD cards mention both the Generation and the target performance segments in their model number. See below,

For nVidia
------------
First number is Series, last 2 numbers give performance segment.

Eg, Geforce 610 = 6th series, 10 = Lowest performace card in this generation.
Geforce 630 = 6th series, 30 = Medium performance
Geforce 660 = 6th series, 60 = High performance, and similarly 690 = Extremely high performance.

Also note that older generations high end cards will still DESTROY new generations low end cards. Eg, a Geforce 480 will kill a Geforce 610 :)

For ATi/AMD Radeon
------------------------
First number is Series, last 3 numbers give performance segment.

Eg- HD 7970, 7th series, 970 means Extremely high end
HD 7750, 7th series,750 means high end
HD 6670, 6th series, 670 means medium performance
HD 6450, 6th series, 450 Low end card
